{"questionId":"22462056","questionHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mi>z</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempts to express&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mi>z</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;in the form&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>Re</mi><mo> </mo><mi>z</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>Im</mi><mo> </mo><mi>z</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mi>z</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi></msqrt></math></p>\n<p>attempts to expand&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp;and then uses</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;in an&nbsp;attempt to simplify&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mi>z</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi></msqrt></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mi>z</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>4</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></msqrt><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>AG</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[4 marks]</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><strong>METHOD 2</strong>&nbsp;- covers answers to both parts a(i) and a(ii)</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>M1A1A1</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">attempt to form&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>r</mi><mo> </mo><mi>c</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>s</mi><mi>θ</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>M1</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1A1</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>∴</mo><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mi>z</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>arg</mi><mo> </mo><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>θ</mi></math>.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>AG</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22462056","referenceCode":"24M.2.AHL.TZ2.8aii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"z=2 cos θ.","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.6—Pythagorean identity, double angles","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.12—Complex numbers – Cartesian form and Argand diag","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.13—Polar and Euler form"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}